title: Source, format and save 500 company logos + brand colors
description:
We need help with sourcing and uniformly saving logos of 503 companies and identifying + capturing the HEX value of their main brand color in a spreadsheet.

The task is based on the attached spreadsheet, which contains a list of 503 unique companies (some of them appear more than once). We need square 400×400 images of the companies' logos centered / formatted and saved as PNG and we also need the HEX value of the companies' primary brand color from their H^website^H.

Workflow:

LOGO: You would grab the logo from their Facebook or Twitter profile, or their H^website^H (links in the spreadsheet), drop it into a square canvas in Photoshop, Figma or editor of your choice, make sure it is centered, has a bit of space around it and save it as a PNG file with the filename provided (equal to the domain name of the company's H^website^H)

BRAND COLOR: You would visit the company's H^website^H, identify their main brand color and grab the HEX color value (There are many Chrome extensions with a color picker, or use this one on Mac https://apps.apple.com/us/app/handypalette/id1515022667?mt=12) and paste it into the spreadsheet.

Please see the spreadsheet and attached two logo images for examples of this done for two of the first companies in the list.

The deliverables are:
– ZIP file with 503 400×400 PNG logo images named correctly with company's domain
– spreadsheet with the logo file name and brand HEX color value columns completed

Feel free to go through the workflow for a couple of companies to estimate how long this task will take you, to bid accordingly.

Thank you.
